<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Deceitful" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Deceitful,</orth> 1) full of fallacy, fraudulent: <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.7.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 7, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.4.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 4, 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 1, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.7.109" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 7, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.141" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 3, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 58</bibl>.<lb />2) delusive: <cit><quote>conceit d., so compact, so kind,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1423" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1423</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) disappointing expectation: <cit><quote>they fall their crests and like d. jades sink in the trial,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 4.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 2, 26</bibl></cit>.
